                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d390">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 2126/316.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Furniss</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-11-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 23, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Root acknowledges his telegram of November 21, and directs Mr. Furniss to
                    convey to the Haitian Government the usual notice that blockade must be
                    proclaimed and maintained by an adequate force in order to be respected.</p>
            </div>
